Plain_Text_Content:
LLM Kaggle competition is 1 week to go, final project on the LLM Zoomcamp, upcoming podcasts on career development and urban data science.

View this email in your browser (


** DataTalks.Club Weekly
------------------------------------------------------------
This is a weekly email newsletter to keep you up-to-date about everything happening in our community: our events and other activities.
Join our Slack (


** ML Zoomcamp 2024 Pre-Course Live Q&A
------------------------------------------------------------

Before the start of a new cohort of the ML Zoomcamp, Alexey will host a live Q&A about ML engineering and this course.

He'll cover:
* Course curriculum: what topics and technologies are covered by the course
* ​Course assignments, homework, and getting feedback
* ​Course projects for your portfolio

Prepare your ML engineering questions and register!
Join the Q&A (


** LLM Kaggle Competition: 1 Week to Go
------------------------------------------------------------

Only two weeks are left until the end of the LLM Zoomcamp 2024 Competition.

Got questions or feel nervous? We prepared the materials for you:
* A getting started notebook ( with a 50% score on the leaderboard
* Alexey answered ( how to start a competition

Remember, the goal is to learn and do your best, not necessarily to be the top performer.

Everyone who manages to improve the getting started notebook will receive extra points for the course!
Receive extra points (


** LLM Zoomcamp
------------------------------------------------------------

We are beginning work on the final project!

To help you get started, we have:
* Prepared a bonus module ( with an end-to-end project example
* Scheduled office hours today (Monday), 5 PM CET. Ask your questions here (

Build a final project to apply everything you've learned.
Start your final project (


** MLOps Zoomcamp
------------------------------------------------------------


Congratulations to everyone who passed the first attempt! Now you can get your certificate ( and put it on your LinkedIn.

For those on the second attempt, remember tomorrow is the deadline for peer reviewing.
Review your peers (


** 🎙️ Upcoming Podcast: Using Data to Create Liveable Cities
------------------------------------------------------------

Rachel Lim, an urban data scientist will talk about:
* Using data to enhance livability in cities and urban areas
* Urban data collection and life cycle
* Data types and sources
* Vision for the data-driven future of liveable cities

Rachel Lim integrates data-driven techniques with urban design principles to promote sustainable and equitable urban environments.
Join here (


** 🎙️ Upcoming Podcast: Developing Your Career in ML by Studying
------------------------------------------------------------

Ella (Wati) Sahnan will share her experience about:
* Learning journey
* Mastering the Zoomcamps
* Motivation and time management
* Learning in public

​Ella (Wati) Sahnan is an experienced IT professional with a diverse background. Ella's tech journey spans from early coding in Notepad++ to utilizing AI tools like ChatGPT, yet she remains committed to the core values of ethics and empathy.

Subject: Fwd: Important Update: How to Properly Fold a T-Shirt
Plain_Text_Content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Mann Kurani <mkkurani1@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 24 Aug 2024 at 15:56
Subject: Important Update: How to Properly Fold a T-Shirt
To: <projektkush@gmail.com>


*Hi Alex,*

We know life can get busy, so we thought we’d share something truly
essential—how to fold a T-shirt like a pro. Because, let’s face it,
everyone needs perfectly folded T-shirts, right?
*Step-by-Step Guide:*

   1. *Lay the T-Shirt Flat:* Make sure it's wrinkle-free (or as close as
   possible).
   2. *Fold One Side In:* Bring the sleeve in towards the middle.
   3. *Fold the Other Side:* Repeat on the other side. You should now have
   a long rectangle.
   4. *Fold in Half:* Fold from the bottom up to the collar. Boom! You’ve
   got yourself a neatly folded T-shirt.

*Why This Matters:*

   - *It Really Doesn’t:* But hey, at least your closet will look more
   organized!
   - *Impress Your Friends:* When they see your perfectly folded T-shirts,
   they’ll be amazed—or not.
   - *Save Space:* Actually, this might be the one useful thing here. More
   room for snacks in your dorm!

*Bonus Tip:*

   - *The Roll Method:* For the truly adventurous, try rolling your
   T-shirts instead. It’s less conventional, but who needs conventions anyway?

Thanks for tuning in to this absolutely critical update. We know you’re now
equipped with the knowledge to conquer your laundry like never before.

Until next time, stay folded!

*Best regards,*
The Totally Unnecessary Tips Team

(555) 987-6543
